2000-01-01|2000-12-30.description:
Overview
As time runs out on their ill-fated mission to arrest fifty "technocriminals" in 100 minutes, Kei and Yuri have themselves been captured by their sinister prey! Not only have the tables been turned, but Yuri is in danger of ending up on the table, as "Planarian cannibals" intend to consume her nubile flesh in a spicy (but low-fat) stir-fry dish! Could this be (gasp)... THE END for The Dirty Pair?
2000-01-01|2000-12-30.name: Daughter of the Sun Goddess

volume.name: The Dirty Pair: Run From the Future

Darth Sidious sends the merciless Darth Maul to destroy Black Sun.A intergalactic criminal organization.Darth

Mauls journey begins by entering a space station owned by the Black Sun vigo Darnada Darth Maul goes there and later killed Feen Fennoob who was wanted for not payong his depts.Darth Maul went undercover and was taken to Darnada himself by Asa Naga there he said infront of Darnadas face "i'm here to kill you"!Darth Maul battles his bodyguard Sinya he kills her and Darnada.He later let Asa go so he could tell the leader and the other vigos.Darth Maul blows the station up and goes for the rest of Black Sun.Darth Maul later interogates one of the vigos the vigo then tells him that you can find the rest of Balck Sun on the planet Rallitiir.The vigo later ask Maul if he can spare him. Maul says "No" and kills him.Maul then came to the Black Sun base of operations and One by one kills all of the vigos.Alexi Garyn[leader of Black Sun]and his bodyguard Mighella escape but Mighella stays and confronts Maul theysfought and Maul cut her in half.Maul then hunts for Garyn who was about to escape Maul drowend Garyn and escapes.
2000-01-01|2000-12-30.name: Part Four

2000-01-01|2000-12-30.description: Events come to an inevitable head as alliances are made and broken while battle lines are drawn. Ghost wants to destroy Malcolm Greymater's "Resurrection Engine." Batgirl wants to bring Two-Face to justice. Two-Face wants Greymater out of Gotham City, and Greymater wants Ghost. It all comes down to Ghost and Batgirl versus Two-Face and his henchmen versus Greymater and his forces -- a three-way showdown from which nobody walks away unscathed!
2000-01-01|2000-12-30.name: The Resurrection Engine (Part Four)

2000-01-01|2000-12-30.description: Wedding Day! But as the guests are taking their places, the Imperial's disruption of the festivities begins! Swoop riders are raiding the building and a madman with a vest-full of explosives is threatening to take the entire building down! Who can save the saviors of the galaxy?
2000-01-01|2000-12-30.name: Part 4 of 4

2000-01-01|2000-12-30.description: Eisner Award winners Sergio Aragonés and Mark Evanier bring the latest chapter in the life of Groo the Wanderer to a close. Relmihio, the cowardly, conniving son of the Pipil Khan must behead Groo to assume his father's throne, and he has a foolproof plan how to do it. Unfortunately for him, it may be that no plan is foolproof enough to thwart the fool known as Groo.

volume.name: Sergio Aragonés' Groo: Mightier Than the Sword

2000-01-01|2000-12-30.description: Why does Fran sleep with a butcher knife? What happens when a New York hipster moves to a small community in Florida? Bandages, crutches, pain pills, and terror-just another day in Collier County! Clover Honey creator Rich Tommaso will keep you on the edge of your seat in this penultimate chapter to his five-issue series. Be there or be square for "The Return Of Day Of The Dumb"!
